control-z — third-party notices
===============================

The code in this repository is MIT (see LICENSE). The tools also download
machine-learning models on first use. Those models are NOT part of this
repository and carry their own licenses — all permissive, never CC-BY-NC,
never gated behind a login. Each shows its license card before downloading,
is verified against a pinned SHA-256, and is listed with its license on the
Suite's Models page.

  YuNet face detection (OpenCV Zoo)        MIT
  YOLOX-s person detection (Megvii)        Apache-2.0
  SAM 2.1 hiera-small (Meta)               Apache-2.0
  MiDaS-small (Intel ISL)                  MIT
  Real-ESRGAN x2/x4 (xinntao)              BSD-3-Clause
  Whisper via faster-whisper (Systran)     MIT
  pyannote segmentation-3.0                MIT
  3D-Speaker embeddings                    Apache-2.0
  DeepFilterNet 3 (optional binary)        MIT/Apache-2.0 dual

The policy that keeps this list permissive — and the models deliberately
rejected for their licenses — is in specs/00-overview.md. The pinned registry
is czcore/models.py.

Demo imagery on control-z.org comes from freely-licensed Pexels clips; the
site footer credits the creators. Site sources: site/make_slides.py documents
the footage rule.
